The rich cultural diversity of Mpumalanga was on full display when the Mpumalanga Cultural Xperience started with a Street Parade on the streets of Mbombela CBD on Friday morning. The Street Parade featured soldiers, cops, dance troupes, clowns and school pupils. The 4th Cultural Xperience aims to bring together the diverse people of the province to celebrate in song, dance and also attract visitors from outside to revel in the beauty of the province. This yearâ€™s programme is designed to bring the whole family together and also the different racial groups under one roof to celebrate the best that the province has to offer. 